implements org.apache.orc.CompressionCodec, org.apache.orc.impl.DirectDecompressionCodec
    orc ZstdCodec.

    NOTE: The file was copied and modified to support zstd-jni. This feature is only supported in ORC 2.0, but 2.0 only supports JDK17. We need to support JDK8.

      • compress

        public boolean compress(ByteBuffer in,
                        ByteBuffer out,
                        ByteBuffer overflow,
                        Options options)
                 throws IOException
        Compresses an input ByteBuffer into an output ByteBuffer using Zstandard compression. If the maximum bound of the number of output bytes exceeds the output ByteBuffer size, the remaining bytes are written to the overflow ByteBuffer.
        Parameters:
        in - the bytes to compress
        out - the compressed bytes
        overflow - put any additional bytes here
        options - the options to control compression
        Returns:
        ZstdOptions
        Throws:
        IOException
